      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented regression test suite covering hemolysis constitutive model; independent code review completed.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM 9) is version-controlled and regression tests exist for core fluid solvers, but the custom hemolysis damage accumulation library lacks an independent regression suite. Only informal internal review was conducted. Achieved level 2 against required level 4 for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to hemolysis transport equation; order-of-accuracy confirmed for all governing equations.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was applied to the Navier-Stokes equations and confirmed second-order spatial accuracy. The hemolysis power-law damage model was not subjected to MMS; analytical solution comparison is absent. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation on three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% for NIH quantity of interest.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (2M, 8M, 32M cells) were generated. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI of 18% for NIH at the highest-shear operating point, exceeding the 5% threshold. Mesh refinement study was not repeated for all 5 operating conditions. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions fully documented including fluid temperature, hematocrit, anticoagulant protocol, and pump priming procedure; traceability to ASTM F1841 confirmed.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data documents flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity. Hematocrit variability across test runs is reported but anticoagulant protocol deviations are noted in footnotes without quantification. ASTM F1841 traceability is partial. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., E% with uncertainty bounds) computed for NIH at each operating point; statistical equivalence test performed.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error computed as 38% across 5 operating points. No formal statistical equivalence test was performed. Prediction intervals from the Monte Carlo UQ campaign are wide (spanning 1.8× experimental mean) but are reported descriptively rather than used in a formal acceptance test. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
