      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "NIH directly maps to clinical hemolysis threshold; correspondence between model output and clinical endpoint formally documented.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the standard hemolysis metric and maps directly to the clinical endpoint. Correspondence is acknowledged in the submission but formal documentation of the NIH-to-plasma-free-hemoglobin clinical translation is absent. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation performed on geometry, operating conditions, and fluid properties representative of the VAD COU; gaps formally bounded.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA generic pump geometry, which differs from the specific VAD impeller geometry. Operating conditions partially overlap COU2 duty envelope but VAD-specific high-speed operating points (>4500 rpm) are not covered in the validation dataset. Relevance gap is acknowledged but not formally bounded. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria documented and demonstrated sufficient for NIH QoI; round-off error analysis performed.",
      "rationale": "Residual convergence targets were set to 1e-5 for momentum and continuity; NIH-specific convergence was not monitored. No round-off error analysis was conducted. Factor flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1; not formally assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation workflow with peer review of boundary condition setup, material property assignment, and post-processing scripts.",
      "rationale": "No independent peer review of the simulation setup was conducted. Boundary condition assignment and post-processing scripts were authored by a single analyst without documented cross-check. Flagged as epistemic gap. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification for choice of hemolysis constitutive model (power-law vs. strain-based) with comparison to alternative model forms; sensitivity to model form quantified.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was selected without documented comparison to alternative constitutive forms (e.g., Arora mechanistic model). Model-form uncertainty is unquantified. The Monte Carlo UQ campaign treated constitutive parameters as uncertain but held model form fixed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs characterized with probability distributions; distributions justified from literature or measurement; input uncertainty propagated through Monte Carlo.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ (N=2000 LHS samples) propagated uncertainty in inlet velocity profile, fluid viscosity, and power-law exponent. Distributions for viscosity were drawn from literature without device-specific measurement. Rotational speed uncertainty was treated as deterministic. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
