      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sample size justification for experimental replicates; statistical power analysis confirming sufficient replicates to characterize NIH variability.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark dataset provides 3 replicates per operating point. No statistical power analysis was conducted to confirm adequacy of replicate count for NIH variability characterization at VAD operating conditions. Flagged as epistemic gap. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal mapping between experimental test fluid properties and physiological blood properties documented; equivalency criteria met or deviation bounded.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used porcine blood with hematocrit 33±2%; COU2 targets human blood at physiological hematocrit 40–45%. Equivalency of rheological properties across this range was not formally assessed. The deviation in power-law parameters between porcine and human blood is unquantified in the package. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
